The paper discusses the use of advanced image reconstruction techniques for dynamic PET images, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and image processing (cs.IM). The use of sparse penalty models and optimization algorithms also suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the simulation and analysis of the phantom data involves the use of mathematical models and statistical methods, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
